2. Get API Keys From Your Broker

API keys play a vital role in connecting your master and child accounts to the trading software.

For each account, you need to:

Log in to the broker (Zerodha, Angel One, Alice Blue, etc.)

Create the API key

Keep safe the API key + secret key

The keys function like a secured tunnel through which automated trade execution can flow.

3. Establish Your Main & Dependent Accounts

After getting the API keys, make a decision regarding:

Master Account → The one where trades are going to be executed

Dependent Accounts → Accounts that will observe trades

It is important that all accounts are financed with respect to your plan and risk appetite.

Get more information  from here:https://copytrading.combiz.org/contact

4. Connect Accounts Within the Copy Trading Program

For instance, in Combiz, the linking procedure is very easy:

Input Master account with API keys

Input each Dependent account with its own API keys

Check connection status

Merge Dependent accounts with the Master account

In a matter of seconds, all accounts are ready for automatic copying.

5. Set Up Copy Trading Options

It's time to set up the trade mirroring for each account as follows:

✔ Volume / Lot Multiplier

1x → Exact trade size

0.5x → Half size

2x → Double the Master’s trade

This technique helps in risk balancing across accounts.

✔ Risk Settings

Automatic stop-loss

Automatic take-profit

Maximum loss per day

Lot scaling

✔ Optional Staggering (Prop Firms)

If necessary, delay the trades by 1–3 seconds in order to avoid prop firm bypass flags.

6. Turn on Auto Copy & Track Performance

After the settings have been applied:

Switch ON the auto-copy mode

All trades from the Master account will be reflected instantly on all Child accounts

Daily performance monitoring

Adjusting multipliers in case of necessity

Weekly review of the strategy

